    },
    {
      "title": "Technology & Architecture Decisions",
      "content": "Stack selection prioritizes operational familiarity and minimal cognitive load: Spring Boot for all three new services (leveraging existing Java expertise from the monolith), Docker containers for packaging, Kubernetes or managed infrastructure (ECS, GKE) for orchestration. Message queue is RabbitMQ (chosen over Kafka for lower operational overhead during early phases; can migrate to Kafka later if event volume demands it). Each service gets its own PostgreSQL instance or schema (dual-write strategy for data migrations, not eventual consistency without testing). Monitoring is Prometheus + Grafana (free, battle-tested, no new licensing). Service mesh (Istio) is explicitly deferred to year 2\u2014it's a distraction in month 1. Infrastructure decision prioritizes staging environment parity with production immediately; integration bugs are caught before production via staged deployment. Async patterns (sagas for payment orchestration) are introduced carefully: Phase 1-2 use synchronous calls + logging before moving to events. This trades latency for debuggability and reduced distributed transaction complexity during the learning phase.",
